16/06/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- An explosion injured nine people late Sunday (June 15th) at a cafe in the Buyukcekmece quarter in Istanbul's European section. 
The blast broke windows and destroyed a car parked nearby. 
Witnesses tentatively attributed the explosion to a percussion bomb.
In another incident, a bus overturned in Samsun province in northern Turkey early Monday, killing three and injuring 38. 
The bus fell into a deep ravine. 
(DHA - 16/06/08; Reuters, CNN Turk, AFP, Anadolu news agency, ITAR-TASS - 15/06/08)
